track_notes: Probably best footpath up El Teide. Parking space is limited at this trail head. A permit to go to the summit is needed. If you stay a night in the hut, the permit is included (as of 2019). Mountain hut needs booking in advance and doesnt serve food. Most people get up very early to see the sunrise from the summit which is probably very crowded. Sometimes strong smell of sulfur. Besides that, perfect 360° view.

A permit to go to the summit is needed, which needs to be applied for additionally to reserve a place in the cable car in advance! The summit is probably very crowded. Sometimes strong smell of sulfur. Besides that, perfect 360° view. NOTE: at this height, altitude sickness already could affect you!
